<h1 class="hero-h">How much does Claude Enterprise cost? <em>2026 reference.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Anthropic does not publish Claude Enterprise pricing, but the deals we see follow a predictable shape. Here is the typical seat range as of June 2026, what drives it up and down, and how it stacks up against the alternatives.</p>
<div class="verdict"><div class="verdict-l">Short answer</div><p class="verdict-p">Claude Enterprise is custom-priced, typically in the $60 to $200-plus per seat per month range as of June 2026, depending on seat count, usage, and the features you negotiate in. Most organizations under 100 seats are better served by Claude Team unless they specifically need SSO, audit logs, larger context, or custom data terms.</p></div>
<p class="note">Pricing references are as of June 2026 and may change. Always confirm current pricing on the vendor site before committing.</p>
</div></div>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">The pricing tiers</h2>
<p class="body">Anthropic does not publish Enterprise pricing. The deals we see fall into three rough bands:</p>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Lower band (~$60-$90 per seat / month).</strong> Smaller orgs (100 to 500 seats) buying a fairly standard Enterprise package.</li>
<li><strong>Mid band (~$90-$150 per seat / month).</strong> Mid-market deals (500 to a few thousand seats) with negotiated usage envelopes and SSO.</li>
<li><strong>Upper band ($150-$200-plus per seat / month).</strong> Larger deployments with strong data terms, custom retention, or specialized features. Annual commits and prepay can lower this.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">What drives the number up or down</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Seat count.</strong> Larger commits get lower per-seat pricing.</li>
<li><strong>Usage envelope.</strong> Heavy-usage commitments increase the per-seat number.</li>
<li><strong>Data terms.</strong> Stricter retention and redaction commitments often raise the price.</li>
<li><strong>Context window and feature mix.</strong> Pricier when you negotiate in larger context windows or specialized features.</li>
<li><strong>Annual prepay vs monthly.</strong> Annual prepay lowers the effective rate, often substantially.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Where it fits the cost ladder</h2>
<table class="cmp-table">
<thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>Typical cost</th><th>Best when</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>Claude Pro (individual)</td><td>~$20 / month</td><td>Solo users trying paid Claude</td></tr>
<tr><td>Claude Team</td><td>Per-seat published rate</td><td>Small orgs (5 to 50 seats) wanting shared workspace and default no-training terms</td></tr>
<tr><td>Claude Enterprise</td><td>~$60 to $200-plus / seat / month (custom)</td><td>Larger orgs needing SSO, audit, custom data terms, larger context</td></tr>
<tr><td>ChatGPT Enterprise</td><td>Custom, in a similar range</td><td>OpenAI's enterprise tier; comparable feature shape</td></tr>
<tr><td>Microsoft Copilot (M365)</td><td>Per-seat published rate</td><td>Microsoft 365-aligned teams</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Who should pay for it</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Pay for Enterprise if</strong> you need SSO, audit logs, dedicated support, custom retention, or larger context as a hard requirement.</li>
<li><strong>Stay on Team if</strong> your needs are shared workspace, central billing, and default no-training data terms.</li>
<li><strong>Wait if</strong> a smaller group is the only one with real use; let them prove value on Pro or Team first.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Frequently asked questions</h2>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What is the public price of Claude Enterprise?</div><div class="faq-a">There is not one. Anthropic prices Claude Enterprise via custom quotes. The typical band as of June 2026 is roughly $60 to $200-plus per seat per month.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Is Claude Enterprise cheaper than ChatGPT Enterprise?</div><div class="faq-a">They are in the same general band as of June 2026. Differences are smaller than the differences in your team's preferences, existing tools, and negotiated terms.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Do we need Enterprise or is Team enough?</div><div class="faq-a">Most organizations under 100 seats get more value from Team unless SSO, audit logs, custom data terms, or larger context are real requirements.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How much can we negotiate?</div><div class="faq-a">Multi-year prepays, large seat commits, and willingness to be a reference customer all create room for negotiation.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How current is this estimate?</div><div class="faq-a">As of June 2026. Vendor pricing changes; confirm with Anthropic sales before budgeting.</div></div>
</div></section>

